<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" style="margin: 0px 0px 1em;" data-reactid="12">The Indiana House recently passed&#194;&#160;Senate Bill 52&#194;&#160;by a unanimous vote of 93-0. SB-52 legalizes hemp-derived CBD oil with no more than 0.3 percent THC. Similar legislation,&#194;&#160;House Bill 1214, recently passed the Senate Corrections and Criminal Law Committee by a 6-2 vote. Differences between the bills will need to be resolved before it heads to the governor&#226;&#128;&#153;s desk for his signature. In addition, the state&#226;&#128;&#153;s&#194;&#160;House Bill 1137&#194;&#160;would establish an industrial hemp pilot program.</p>
<p class="canvas-atom canvas-text Mb(1.0em) Mb(0)--sm Mt(0.8em)--sm" data-reactid="13">&#226;&#128;&#156;We support Indiana&#226;&#128;&#153;s latest legislative actions that bring the state one step closer to legalizing hemp-derived CBD oil and creating an infrastructure for a viable hemp program that can create jobs and spur economic activity,&#226;&#128;&#157; said Hemp, Inc. CEO Bruce Perlowin.</p>
