INSERT INTO articles VALUES (12689, 'Is Cannabis a Natural Way to Boost Cycling Performance?', NULL, 'eva2.jpg', '<div class="post-content-right">
			<div class="post-content description " itemprop="articleBody">
			
				
								
							
								
					<p><span style="font-weight: 400">CANNABIS CULTURE &#8211; The</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Anti-Doping_Agency"><span style="font-weight: 400"> WADA (World Anti-Doping Agency)</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> prohibits cannabinoids (grown cannabis and its derivatives) and cannabimimetics (Spice and other synthesised cannabis substitutes) for use in competition. </span><span id="more-69903"></span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">This puts cannabis in the same company as more conventionally well-known doping narcotics like opioids, ephedrine and anabolic steroids. However, this has not stopped KYND Cannabis Company sponsoring professional cyclist Teal Stetson-Lee in Nevada, helped by the state legalising recreational marijuana consumption in 2016. It&#8217;s a strange position for an athlete to find themselves in, but points to the fact that a broader trend towards decriminalising marijuana could see the world of dope and the world of cycling develop an unlikely relationship.</span></p>
<p><b>A Gray Area</b></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">In 2009 former </span><a href="http://vuelta.club/"><span style="font-weight: 400">w</span></a><a href="http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/missy-giove-from-world-champion-to-convict-and-back-again/"><span style="font-weight: 400">orld champion mountain biker Melissa Giove</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> was busted for possession of roughly 350 pounds of cannabis. Indeed, federally cannabis is still classified as an illegal narcotic. Indeed, cannabis is a schedule one narcotic, which places it in the same category as &#8220;hard drugs.&#8221; However, cannabis has an ever more vocal chorus of patients and scientists preaching the innumerable medicinal qualities of this plant. The scientific community has been taking more serious investigations into the benefits of certain types of cannabis molecules to treat various mental and physical ailments, and as the possibilities of health benefits become grounded in more legitimate research, it&#8217;s no wonder mainstream media publications are also slowly destigmatising their coverage of cannabis use. Of course, there&#8217;s </span><a href="http://vuelta.club/"><span style="font-weight: 400">a</span></a> <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4417655/"><span style="font-weight: 400">wide variety of different kinds of cannabis</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> with varying degrees of effectiveness, with treatment also being contingent on the size of the dose, type of cannabinoid used and method of application. What possible benefits could this bear on cyclists?</span></p>
<p><b><img class=" wp-image-69905 alignleft" src="https://www.cannabisculture.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/bike-242x350.jpg" alt="" width="413" height="597" srcset="https://www.cannabisculture.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/bike-242x350.jpg 242w, https://www.cannabisculture.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/bike.jpg 496w, https://www.cannabisculture.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/bike-242x350@2x.jpg 484w" sizes="(max-width: 413px) 100vw, 413px">The Survey Says&#8230;</b></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
<p><a href="https://www.medicaljane.com/2014/06/13/chronic-pain-and-the-theraputic-benefits-of-medical-cannabis/"><span style="font-weight: 400">Marijuana&#8217;s ability to treat chronic pain</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> is one of the better-researched aspects of potential medical applications. This could certainly benefit cyclists looking to pass further through the pain barrier for extended periods of cycling. Certain types of cannabinoid receptors, principally CB1 and CB2, which when triggered can result in an increase in somatic cardiovascular capacity through a process known as angiogenesis. The ability to send more blood to vital organs boast an obvious appeal to cycling enthusiasts. CB2 receptors can also regulate nitrous oxide generation, which helps cells activate in low-oxygen conditions. This can benefit any athlete, but the boost to high altitude mountain bikers is particularly interesting. It&#8217;s not all good news, though: THC has been found to increase a person&#8217;s resting heart rate and diminish the heart&#8217;s productivity during periods of extended exertion. It&#8217;s also found to increase blood pressure with short-term use. Although long-term use can see a drop over time, it also leads to a greater risk of hypotension. </span></p>
<p><strong>The Verdict</strong></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Ultimately, the consensus on whether cannabis use could benefit physical activities like cycling hasn&#8217;t been reached. There still needs to be much more high-level research on the issue. Thankfully, with changing attitudes, that looks to be more of a likelihood in the future. Even then, the decision will come down to personal preference. The same dose and strain of marijuana can have very different effects on two different people, and tolerance and the background of a person&#8217;s general mental health also has a big impact on the results of cannabis consumption. It&#8217;s too early to say, in other words, but it looks to be a fascinating research topic for some time to come.</span></p>
<p>&#160;</p>
	
								
			</div><!-- .post-content -->
		</div>
		
	', '2018-03-05 00:00:00', 'https://www.cannabisculture.com/content/2018/03/05/cannabis-unique-way-boost-cycling-performance', 6, '2018-03-05 20:20:21.766319', '2018-03-07 01:34:52.506485', 13, NULL, NULL, 0, 'is-cannabis-a-natural-way-to-boost-cycling-performance');
INSERT INTO articles VALUES (12692, 'Challenge to Florida ban on smokable medical marijuana gets May trial date', NULL, 'florida-medical-marijuana-lawsuit-attorney-john-morgan-800x496.jpg', '<div class="entry-content">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="large-10 large-centered small-12 columns">
                        <div class="entry-meta-date">Published: <time class="entry-date" datetime="2018-03-05T13:37:59-0700" pubdate>Mar 5, 2018, 1:37 pm</time> &#8226; Updated: <time class="entry-date updated timeago" datetime="2018-03-05T13:37:59-0700">Mar 5, 2018, 1:37 pm</time> <span class="single-comments-link"><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/03/05/florida-medical-marijuana-smokable-ban-trial-date/100530/#disqus_thread" class="commentsNameLink"></a></span></div>                        <p class="byline">By <span class="author"><a class="url fn n" href="https://www.thecannabist.co/author/ap/" rel="author">The Associated Press</a></span></p>                                                <p>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. &#8212; A hearing on Florida banning smokable forms of medical marijuana will be heard by a circuit court judge in May.</p>
<p>Leon County Judge Karen Gievers will hold a non-jury trial on May 16 to determine if the ban violates the <a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2017/06/26/florida-medical-marijuana-rules-legilsation/82406/">2016 state constitutional amendment</a> that legalized medical marijuana.</p>
<p>People United for Medical Marijuana, which is the committee formed by Orlando attorney John Morgan, <a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2017/07/07/florida-medical-marijuana-smokable-ban-lawsuit-john-morgan/83260/">filed the lawsuit last July</a> against the state&#8217;s Department of Health.</p>
<div class="large-6 medium-12 small-12 columns right sidebox related"><hr><h4>Related stories</h4><ul><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/02/28/medical-marijuana-dispensaries-florida/99642/" rel="bookmark" title="Colorado cannabis company to expand in Florida county despite marijuana moratorium">Colorado cannabis company to expand in Florida county despite marijuana moratorium</a></li><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/02/21/medical-marijuana-conquered-opioid-addiction/99620/" rel="bookmark" title="Medical marijuana conquered my 30-year opioid addiction, Florida man says">Medical marijuana conquered my 30-year opioid addiction, Florida man says</a></li><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2017/09/19/sarasota-florida-medical-marijuana-dispensaries/88313/" rel="bookmark" title="Sarasota, Florida plotting workaround to comply with state MMJ laws">Sarasota, Florida plotting workaround to comply with state MMJ laws</a></li></ul><hr></div>
<p><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2016/01/27/florida-medical-marijuana-november-2016-ballot/47293/">Morgan spearheaded</a> the constitutional amendment, which was <a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2016/11/08/florida-medical-marijuana-results-amendment-2-election-2016/66816/">approved by 71 percent of voters</a>.</p>
<p>The state legislature banned smoking in last year&#8217;s bill <a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2017/06/26/florida-medical-marijuana-rules-legilsation/82406/">signed by Gov. Rick Scott</a>, saying it isn&#8217;t healthy. The law <a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2017/06/19/florida-medical-marijuana-law-rules/81887/">does allow for vaping, edibles, oils, sprays or tinctures</a>.</p>
<p>There are eight cases against the state, ranging from smoking to how the state awards licenses for medical marijuana treatment centers.</p>
<div data-spotim-module="recirculation" data-spot-id="sp_4iGOdl8H"></div>
</div>
                </div><!-- .row -->
            </div>', '2018-03-05 00:00:00', 'https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/03/05/florida-medical-marijuana-smokable-ban-trial-date/100530/', 4, '2018-03-05 20:55:23.646791', '2018-03-07 16:02:09.070029', 12, NULL, NULL, 0, 'challenge-to-florida-ban-on-smokable-medical-marijuana-gets-may-trial-date');
INSERT INTO articles VALUES (12701, '4 Ways to Make Sure Your Smoking Kit Won’t Let You Down', NULL, 'smoking_kit.jpg', '<section class="cb-entry-content entry-content clearfix" itemprop="articleBody"><p>There&#8217;s an old saying that goes, &#8216;If it&#8217;s not tied on, it&#8217;s gone&#8217;. If you&#8217;re prone to being disorganized, then this might hit very close to home. There are those aberrations of people who seem to have everything filled and locked down, they&#8217;re never late, never lost, and their socks always match. This monastic level of organization probably doesn&#8217;t come naturally to too many of us, and there&#8217;s something comforting in a little chaos.</p><p>There&#8217;s some things, however, that you want to keep as tidy and organized as possible, your love life, your wallet, and your smoking kit. There&#8217;s nothing worse than sitting down to roll and finding that you misplaced your papers, your grinder, or, perish the thought, your herb.</p><p>The average smoking kit has a whole host of components that are worryingly easy to misplace or lose. For one thing you have your papers, your grinder (which is often multi-part), a packing tool, roaches, maybe a pipe, and of course your herb. If you just have that stuff lying around loose it&#8217;s far too easy to lose it. The last thing you need when you want to relax with a joint is the stress of finding you lost a vital part of your smoking kit.</p><p>If you want to avoid this stress, then there&#8217;s a few steps you can take to help yourself become a bit more organised. Nothing too transformative, there&#8217;s no need to transform yourself into a sterile human-filofax. It&#8217;s just a few tips that will save you a little stress.</p><h3><a href="https://the420times.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_interior.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-43245" src="https://the420times.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_interior-300x200.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="400" srcset="http://3s0ugl1qamwo3v5dm83nwpw0.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_interior-300x200.jpg 300w, http://3s0ugl1qamwo3v5dm83nwpw0.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_interior-768x513.jpg 768w, http://3s0ugl1qamwo3v5dm83nwpw0.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_interior-360x240.jpg 360w, http://3s0ugl1qamwo3v5dm83nwpw0.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_interior-600x400.jpg 600w, http://3s0ugl1qamwo3v5dm83nwpw0.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_interior.jpg 878w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px"></a></h3><h3>Get A Case for Your Smoking Kit</h3><p>The best way to keep your smoking kit together is to keep it in a dedicated carrying case. If you only smoke in the privacy of your own home, then the case is ideal as it saves you from rummaging around your room for that pack of paper that you swear you left just there this morning. If you&#8217;re out and about then a good case will stop any loose bits from your kit from going rogue on your travels.</p><p><a href="https://www.everyonedoesit.com/products/the-very-happy-kit?utm_source=the420times&amp;utm_medium=sponsored-adv&amp;utm_campaign=happykit-run1">The Very Happy Kit</a> is an ideal example of a bespoke smoking kit. It&#8217;s everything you could need, it has a solid, discrete exterior, a whole range of handy pockets, straps, and pouches.</p><p>The Very Happy Kit really comes in handy when you want to carry it when you&#8217;re out and about. Its case is fully smell proof, so if you value discreteness, or if you prefer to keep your clothes free from the aroma of your herb then this is invaluable. While we all love the smell of our weed, we don&#8217;t need that potent odor sticking to our clothes or hair.</p><p>On top of all this <a href="https://www.everyonedoesit.com/collections/happy-kit?utm_source=the420times&amp;utm_medium=sponsored-adv&amp;utm_campaign=happykit-run1">the Happy Kit</a> is perfect for first time smokers; it comes bundled with everything you need to put together a great smoking kit. When you first open it up you&#8217;ll find some papers, roaches, a carrying tube for a pre-rolled joint, a plastic grinder with sifter screen, and even a full glass pipe! If you&#8217;re a more experienced smoker, then simply swap out The Very Happy Kit&#8217;s contents for your own materials of choice.</p><h3>Cut Down On Your Kits Individual Components</h3><p>Simply put, the more you have in your kit, the more you have to lose. It&#8217;s easy to stuff your kit to the gills with everything you think you might need for a good smoke, but this can just lead to a bulky kit and more opportunities to misplace something you really need. If you want a kit that won&#8217;t let you down, then you need to trim some of the fat.</p><p>The big questions are the easiest to answer, what do you prefer? Hand-rolled joints or a well-packed pipe? This is what you&#8217;ll be building your kit around, so it&#8217;s an important question! The next thing you need to do is get rid of anything you don&#8217;t use often; do you really need three different sizes of rolling paper? Do you really need filters and a roach book? Finally, try to get multi use items, get a combination pack of skins and roaches, or a grinder/storage jar combo.</p><h3>Get Rid of The Rubbish</h3><p>Once you get your kit up and running it&#8217;s easy to think your job is done but keeping your kit in peak condition is an ongoing task. Over time you&#8217;ll find that empty boxes of skins will build up, along with used up roach books, and of course grime and ash can build up too. Clearing out anything that&#8217;s used up is a must if you want to make sure that your kit will serve you well, the last thing you want is to open up your case to find nothing but empty wrappers and ash in side it.</p><p>So from time to time make sure that your skins are topped up, the ash is wiped out, and your pipe is clean and its airpath free and easy to use!</p><h3><a href="https://the420times.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_outdoor.jpg"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-43246" src="https://the420times.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_outdoor.jpg" alt="" width="599" height="400" srcset="http://3s0ugl1qamwo3v5dm83nwpw0.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_outdoor.jpg 878w, http://3s0ugl1qamwo3v5dm83nwpw0.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_outdoor-300x200.jpg 300w, http://3s0ugl1qamwo3v5dm83nwpw0.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_outdoor-768x513.jpg 768w, http://3s0ugl1qamwo3v5dm83nwpw0.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_outdoor-360x240.jpg 360w, http://3s0ugl1qamwo3v5dm83nwpw0.wpengine.netdna-cdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/smoking_kit_outdoor-600x400.jpg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 599px) 100vw, 599px"></a></h3><h3>Make Sure Your Kit Is Fit For Purpose</h3><p>It&#8217;s tempting to grab any old container or bag that looks big enough to fit your smoking kit. I&#8217;ve seen old iPhone boxes, tupperware, and even old headphone bags used to keep a smoking kit together. These all work fine, until they don&#8217;t. They&#8217;re not intended to be any kind of portable case, never mind for your smoking kit. Sooner or later, they&#8217;ll go to pieces and spill your smoking kit&#8217;s contents out!</p><p>If you&#8217;re going to build a smoking kit then go the extra mile and get a bespoke case. <a href="https://www.everyonedoesit.com/products/the-very-happy-kit?utm_source=the420times&amp;utm_medium=sponsored-adv&amp;utm_campaign=happykit-run1">The Very Happy Kit</a> is an ideal example, it was built from the ground up to be a smoking kit and has taken the dat-to-day trials of the life of a smoking kit into account. It&#8217;s smell proof, and sturdy which makes it ideal for everyday use. It will hold your kit together and wont go to pieces.</p><p>In the end, spending the money on a decent case can save you a lot of stress in the long term.</p><div style="text-align: center">  <noscript><a href="http://the420times.com/openx/www/delivery/ck.php?n=a6be1a87&amp;cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE" target="_blank"><img src="http://the420times.com/openx/www/delivery/avw.php?zoneid=2&amp;cb=INSERT_RANDOM_NUMBER_HERE&amp;n=a6be1a87" border="0" alt=""></a></noscript></div></section>', '2018-03-05 00:00:00', 'https://the420times.com/2018/03/4-ways-to-make-sure-your-smoking-kit-wont-let-you-down/', 11, '2018-03-06 06:31:52.633842', '2018-03-07 18:49:57.174882', 11, NULL, NULL, 0, '4-ways-to-make-sure-your-smoking-kit-won-t-let-you-down');
INSERT INTO articles VALUES (12486, 'Oregon man accused of shipping $1M in marijuana in fake rocks faces federal charge', NULL, 'ThinkstockPhotos-119013360-800x533.jpg', '<div class="entry-content">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="large-10 large-centered small-12 columns">
                        <div class="entry-meta-date">Published: <time class="entry-date" datetime="2018-02-26T04:20:53-0700" pubdate>Feb 26, 2018, 4:20 am</time> &#8226; Updated: <time class="entry-date updated timeago" datetime="2018-02-25T23:28:31-0700">Feb 25, 2018, 11:28 pm</time> <span class="single-comments-link"><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/02/26/oregon-marijuana-shipping-fake-rocks-federal-charge/99942/#disqus_thread" class="commentsNameLink"></a></span></div>                        <p class="byline">By <span class="author"><a class="url fn n" href="https://www.thecannabist.co/author/ap/" rel="author">The Associated Press</a></span></p>                                                <p>PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) &#8212; A 37-year-old man <a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2017/11/15/oregon-marijuana-shipping-fake-rocks/92459/">accused of stashing $1 million worth of marijuana in fake boulders</a> and attempting to ship it from Springfield, Oregon, to Oklahoma City now faces facing a federal charge.</p>
<p>The Oregonian/OregonLive reports that a federal complaint filed Friday in U.S. District Court in Eugene accuses Curran Manzer of possession with intent to distribute more than 100 pounds of marijuana.</p>
<div class="large-6 medium-12 small-12 columns right sidebox related"><hr><h4>Related stories</h4><ul><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/02/15/nebraska-marijuana-seized-sleeping-woman/99172/" rel="bookmark" title="Nebraska police find 70 lbs. of marijuana when woman falls asleep in car at gas station">Nebraska police find 70 lbs. of marijuana when woman falls asleep in car at gas station</a></li><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/02/14/tennessee-cbd-candy-crush/99448/" rel="bookmark" title="Tennessee cops shutter 23 stores accused of selling CBD candy">Tennessee cops shutter 23 stores accused of selling CBD candy</a></li><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/02/09/miami-marijuana-raid-cash-seizure/98639/" rel="bookmark" title="Cops seized $22 million in marijuana cash from a Miami hydroponics shop owner. He won&#8217;t lose it all">Cops seized $22 million in marijuana cash from a Miami hydroponics shop owner. He won&#8217;t lose it all</a></li><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/01/30/marijuana-edibles-toronto-police/97820/" rel="bookmark" title="Report: Toronto police officers consume seized marijuana edibles on the job, one climbs tree">Report: Toronto police officers consume seized marijuana edibles on the job, one climbs tree</a></li><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/01/22/marijuana-nebraska-state-patrol-seizure/97250/" rel="bookmark" title="Nebraska State Patrol seize 122 pounds of marijuana after package falls off flatbed">Nebraska State Patrol seize 122 pounds of marijuana after package falls off flatbed</a></li></ul><hr></div>
<p>A probable cause document says Springfield police began investigating Manzer after the United Parcel Service discovered Manzer attempting to ship packages out of state that smelled of marijuana.</p>
<p>Documents say UPS inspected packages addressed to Manzer and discovered about $50,000 in cash and in November, documents say an officer saw Manzer drop off packages at UPS and that when searching the packages, police found large fake boulders with vacuum-sealed plastic bags of pot.</p>
<p>Shipping pot across state lines is prohibited under both federal and state law.</p>
<p>Information from: <a href="http://www.oregonlive.com">The Oregonian/OregonLive</a></p>
<div data-spotim-module="recirculation" data-spot-id="sp_4iGOdl8H"></div>
</div>
