<div class="auth-prov-logos D(tbc) Va(t) " data-reactid="3">GW Pharmaceuticals plc (GWPH) (&#226;&#128;&#156;GW,&#226;&#128;&#157; &#226;&#128;&#156;the Company&#226;&#128;&#157; or &#226;&#128;&#156;the Group&#226;&#128;&#157;), a biopharmaceutical company focused on discovering, developing and commercializing novel therapeutics from its proprietary cannabinoid product platform, today announced that the European Medicines Agency (EMA) has granted orphan drug designation for cannabidiol (CBD) for the treatment of tuberous sclerosis (TS). GW is currently recruiting a Phase 3 clinical trial of Epidiolex<sup>&#194;&#174;</sup>&#194;&#160;(cannabidiol) as an adjunctive therapy for the treatment of seizures associated with TS, with data expected in the second half of 2018. &#194;&#160;Subject to positive results, GW expects to submit regulatory applications in 2019 for Epidiolex in TS in both the U.S. and Europe.</div>
