INSERT INTO articles VALUES (12736, 'Cannabis company eyes massive expansion, adding 50 Colorado locations within the next 3 years', NULL, 'PotExpansion-SDN-030718-3.jpg', '<div class="entry-content">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="large-10 large-centered small-12 columns">
                        <div class="entry-meta-date">Published: <time class="entry-date" datetime="2018-03-07T09:31:29-0700" pubdate>Mar 7, 2018, 9:31 am</time> &#8226; Updated: <time class="entry-date updated timeago" datetime="2018-03-07T09:54:30-0700">Mar 7, 2018, 9:54 am</time> <span class="single-comments-link"><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2018/03/07/founder-green-man-cannabis-expansion-colorado/100677/#disqus_thread" class="commentsNameLink"></a></span></div>                        <p class="byline">By <strong>Eli Pace</strong>, <em> Summit Daily News</em></p>                                                <p class="STND-STND BodyText DropCap">The founder of Green Man Cannabis, a six-time winner of the Cannabis Cup with two dispensaries in Denver, said he wants to build &#8220;the world&#8217;s most powerful cannabis business franchise system&#8221; under a different brand, and Frisco will figure into those designs.</p>
<p class="STND-STND BodyText">Describing a massive expansion plan, <a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/tag/christian-hageseth/">Christian Hageseth</a> said he expects to have 50 locations across Colorado within the next three years, including possible locations in Aspen, Vail and Steamboat Springs. However, new retail sites have &#8220;already been identified&#8221; in Denver and Frisco.</p>
<div class="large-6 medium-12 small-12 columns right sidebox related"><hr><h4>Related stories</h4><ul><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2017/03/10/cannabis-industry-owners-marijuana-business/72539/" rel="bookmark" title="Entering the cannabis industry with a wealth of business know-how">Entering the cannabis industry with a wealth of business know-how</a></li><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2016/11/25/cannabist-show-chris-driessen-openvape-organa-brands-marques-harris-district-8/68166/" rel="bookmark" title="Cannabist Show: He leads one of world&#8217;s biggest marijuana firms; He&#8217;s a former NFL pro who grows ganja">Cannabist Show: He leads one of world&#8217;s biggest marijuana firms; He&#8217;s a former NFL pro who grows ganja</a></li><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2016/06/16/microsoft-marijuana-business/56361/" rel="bookmark" title="Did Microsoft just jump into the marijuana business?">Did Microsoft just jump into the marijuana business?</a></li><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2016/01/20/marijuana-investing-lawmakers-out-of-state-ownership/46945/" rel="bookmark" title="Legalized states taking fresh look at out-of-state marijuana investing">Legalized states taking fresh look at out-of-state marijuana investing</a></li><li><a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2016/01/08/rise-above-social-strategies-lauren-gibbs-mindful-erik-williams/46126/" rel="bookmark" title="Cannabist Show: She&#8217;s a social media pro; He plans national expansion">Cannabist Show: She&#8217;s a social media pro; He plans national expansion</a></li></ul><hr></div>
<p class="STND-STND BodyText">Experiencing early success with medical marijuana in Ohio, Michigan and California, Green Man Cannabis currently has two dispensaries in the Denver area. All of the new locations, however, would operate under the ONE Cannabis brand, said Hageseth, who&#8217;s the CEO.</p>
<p class="STND-STND BodyText">The majority of the 50 locations planned for Colorado would be with independent dispensary owners through franchise agreements, he continued, adding that he&#8217;s interested in expanding through &#8220;strategic franchise partnerships,&#8221; which he sees as the next big step in the marijuana industry, especially since federal law prevents products from being shipped over state lines.</p>
<p>Read the full story at <a href="https://www.summitdaily.com/news/business/founder-of-green-man-cannabis-plans-massive-colorado-expansion/">SummitDaily.com</a></p>
<hr>
<p><strong>Related:&#160;<a href="https://www.thecannabist.co/2016/04/20/cannabis-cup-green-man-christian-hageseth/52363/">This is how a ganjapreneur celebrates his fifth (and sixth) Cannabis Cup wins</a></strong></p>
